1	Use Case [#16]: delete a service
1.1	Description
There are services that are available or offered on the website, and the service is to be removed or cancelled by the admin.
1.2	Level
Sub-Function 
1.3	Trigger
The admin selects the option to edit services and selects remove/delete service.
1.4	Primary Actor
The Primary Actor is the admin who must remove a service/ product from the site.
1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors
Secondary Actors: 
•	Service provider
1.6	Stakeholders 
Stakeholders:
•	Service provider.
•	People who will look for the service.
1.7	Preconditions
The admin [Primary Actor] must have an active internet connection, logged onto the admin site open in the browser, and the service must exist on the browser.
1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Customer views appointments.
2.	Customer appointments are displayed to customer.
1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: service does not exist:
1.	System doesn’t have the service to be deleted.

1.	Alternative: admin can add service.
1.	Service is put on site.
1.10	Post Conditions
1.10.1	Success End Condition
Service is deleted.
1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
The admin is logged out of page. The system logs the delete request and updates the available services.
1.10.3	Failure End Condition
Service is not deleted and continues to be available on site.
1.11	Frequency
Allow admin to delete multiple services at once.
1.12	Special Requirements
Customers that knew the service and needed it will no longer have access to it
1.12.1	Performance
The service should not appear when the admin is done deleting the service, they should be redirected to services page that is updated.
1.12.2	Security
Only admin should be able to delete services.
1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility
Admin edit services page must comply with South African Disabilities Act requirements.
Admin must be able to view page in English, and on any device of choice.
1.12.4	Other

